Sentencas: BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-delta (BZCY7) exhibits adequate proton conductivity as well as sufficient chemical and thermal stability over a wide range of SOFC operating conditions, while layered SmBa0.5Sr0.5Co2O5+delta (SBSC) perovskite demonstrates advanced electrochemical properties based on doped ceria electrolyte.
Titulo: A novel layered perovskite cathode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This research fully takes advantage of these advanced properties and develops novel protonic ceramic membrane fuel cells (PCMFCs) of Ni-BZCY7 vertical bar BZCY7 vertical bar SBSC.
Titulo: A novel layered perovskite cathode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results show that the open-circuit potential of 1.015 V and maximum power density of 533 mW cm(-2) are achieved at 700 degrees C. With temperature increase, the total cell resistance decreases, among which electrolyte resistance becomes increasingly dominant over polarization resistance.
Titulo: A novel layered perovskite cathode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results also indicate that SBSC perovskite cathode is a good candidate for intermediate temperature PCMFC development, while the developed Ni-BZCY7 vertical bar BZCY7 vertical bar SBSC cell is a promising functional material system for next generation SCFCs.
Titulo: A novel layered perovskite cathode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells
